The Smartsheet Model Context Protocol (MCP) server is an integration layer that connects Smartsheet’s REST API to MCP-compliant AI clients, enabling natural-language interaction with your Smartsheet data [1][2][3]. It allows AI models to perform tasks like summarizing sheets, updating rows, managing workspaces, and searching across assets while respecting user permissions [1][4][5].

To use it, register the server in your AI client's configuration using your regional URL and a Smartsheet API token (or OAuth) [6][3].

Example configuration for a client's settings file:

```javascript
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "smartsheet-mcp": {
      "httpUrl": "https://mcp.smartsheet.com",
      "headers": {
        "Authorization": "Bearer ${SMARTSHEET_API_TOKEN}"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Regional URLs include `https://mcp.smartsheet.com` (US), `https://mcp.smartsheet.eu` (EU), and `https://mcp.smartsheet.au` (Australia) [6].
